    "body": "Thank you for the suggestion @TrinhTrungDung. \"Underflow\" is actually used for numbers whose _absolute_ value is too small, such as floating point numbers when they're too small. Negative numbers in integer arithmetic are considered overflow. See [Arithmetic underflow](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic_underflow) and [Integer overflow](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integer_overflow) on Wikipedia.",
